{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\n\nPurge STALE present-tense bash-engine/bash-seam language from CI comments and the\n`_commands` package module docstrings. These describe machinery that no longer exists:\nthe bash test-suite collector was removed, and the bash write seam was retired in Tier D\n(`_seam.append_event`'s OWN function docstring already says: \"Tier D retired the bash\nseam; `rebar._store` is the sole write core\") — yet several MODULE docstrings and CI\ncomments still assert the bash path in present tense, contradicting reality.\n\nVerified stale spots (each confirmed against `origin/main`):\n1. `.github/workflows/test.yml:8` — comment references \"standalone bash suite under\n   `tests/scripts/test-*.sh`, which the `test_bash_suites.py` collector runs\" — BOTH the\n   collector and `tests/scripts/test-*.sh` are GONE (verified: no such files).\n2. `.github/workflows/external-integration.yml:45` — comment claims the fixture\n   \"initializes a git-backed store via the bash engine, which shells out to jq + git\".\n   The engine is Python/in-process now. Reword the comment (do NOT silently drop the jq\n   install unless verified unused — reword its justification instead).\n3. `src/rebar/_commands/leaf.py:1-9` — the WHOLE module docstring (not just line 9) is\n   stale: it claims the functions are \"reached behind `REBAR_LEAF_WRITES=python`\" and\n   \"append through the bash write seam (`_seam.append_event` → `ticket-append-event.sh` →\n   `write_commit_event`) so the locked write path is unchanged until Tier D\", and \"the\n   per-command bash suite passes against either implementation\". All retired.\n4. `src/rebar/_commands/_seam.py:1-11` — the MODULE docstring still says appends route\n   \"through ONE narrow seam — the bash `ticket-append-event.sh` wrapping\n   `write_commit_event`\" and \"Python writes route through the bash core so invariant I5\n   holds\", directly contradicting THIS FILE's own `append_event` docstring. (Discovered\n   during plan review; added to scope.)\n5. `src/rebar/_commands/__init__.py:1-10` — references the \"`ticket-commands.py` engine\n   entrypoint) when `REBAR_LEAF_WRITES=python`\" bash dispatcher path. (Discovered during\n   plan review; added to scope.)\n\n**Out of scope (deliberately NOT purged):** `src/rebar/_store/event_append.py:4` and\n`src/rebar/_store/lock.py:7,22` reference the bash core as documented lineage / the\n`docs/bash-migration.md §6` dual-window interop rule — these are historical/interop\nreferences, not stale present-tense claims, and are left as-is. Legitimate references to\n`docs/bash-migration.md` as a HISTORICAL record are kept everywhere.\n\n## Scope\nReword each of the five stale spots to describe the CURRENT in-process reality (writes go\nthrough `rebar._store.event_append.write_and_push`; the Python tiers + pytest layout for\ntests), keeping any legitimate historical `bash-migration.md` citation. Do not change\nbehavior — comments/docstrings only.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `test.yml` comment no longer references the removed `test_bash_suites.py` collector\n      or `tests/scripts/test-*.sh`; it describes the current pytest layout.\n- [ ] `external-integration.yml` comment no longer claims a \"bash engine … shells out to\n      jq\"; the jq step's justification is reworded (jq kept only if still used).\n- [ ] The `_commands` module docstrings (leaf.py, _seam.py, __init__.py) describe the\n      current in-process `rebar._store` write path, consistent with `_seam.append_event`.\n- [ ] **Completeness proof (in-session, single command):**\n      `grep -rn 'REBAR_LEAF_WRITES\\|ticket-append-event.sh\\|per-command bash suite\\|route through the bash core\\|test_bash_suites\\|bash engine' src/rebar/_commands .github/workflows/test.yml .github/workflows/external-integration.yml`\n      returns NOTHING (all five stale spots purged; `_store` lineage refs are outside this\n      grep's paths and intentionally untouched).\n- [ ] No behavioral change: `make lint && make typecheck && make test` stay green.\n\nFiles: `.github/workflows/test.yml`, `.github/workflows/external-integration.yml`,\n`src/rebar/_commands/leaf.py`, `src/rebar/_commands/_seam.py`,\n`src/rebar/_commands/__init__.py`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783821689617228001,"uuid":"1055e1ec-90ac-48e9-9216-b83c15529bcf"}